Cluster Maintainence:
tolerationSeconds - this option mention how much pod can be in downtime 
kubectl drain node-1 - make node1 to maintainence mode. when you drain a node pods are moving to the worker.
kubectl uncordon node-1 - make the worker after the upgarde to became avialble to cluster. only after uncordon the pods can be move to the worker.
Running the uncordon command on a node will not automatically schedule pods on the node. When new pods are created, they will be placed on node01.
kubectl cordon node-2 - make that new pods cant be scheduled on the this node/worker. like a freeze.

to see on which nodes the deployments are on:
kubectl get pods -o wide

Cluster Upgrade Rules:
kube-apiserver = X Version - Example V.1.10 
Controller and Scheduler Can be X-1 Version = V.1.9 or V.1.10
kubelet and kube proxy can be X-2 Version = V.1.8 or V.1.9 or V.1.10
kubectl can be X+1 > X-1 
kuberenets supports only 3 minors versions back.
to update a cluster we upgrading only from minor version to the next
example from 1.10 -> 1.13
we should upgrade from 1.10 -> 1.11 -> 1.12 -> 1.3
at first we upgrade Masters servers and then Workers.
Startegy to upgrade Cluster:
1. upgrading all the workers togethers
2. upgrading one worker only and moving to others.
3. adding new Workers with the new upgrade and then removing the old one version.

